jgrep is a grep-like utility written in Java.
Features:
  -- Java regular expressions
     (https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html)
  -- Support for RE2J
     (https://github.com/google/re2)
  -- POSIX options
     (http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009604499/utilities/grep.html)
  -- most GNU grep(1) options
     (https://www.gnu.org/software/grep/)
  -- Extensions over GNU grep(1):
     options -O and -8

Documentation:

  -- https://github.com/cheusov/jgrep/blob/master/jar/jgrep.pod
  -- man page after installation

Installation instruction:

  1) install mk-configure (https://github.com/cheusov/mk-configure), for example,
     on Debian/Linux one can run

     # apt-get install mk-configure

  2) install JDK-7, for example, on Debian/Linux one can run

     # apt-get install openjdk-7-jdk

  3) install maven, for example, on Debian/Linux one can run

     # apt-get install maven

  4)
     # mkcmake all
     # mkcmake test
     # mkcmake install
